aterial combinations. The rubber sole materials are designed to absorb enough impact to protect tendons, joints, and muscles from damage. Nike training shoes usually use breathable mesh uppers that are combined with durable rubber soles.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1689112597263" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1689112597263" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">✅ Increased Performance</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1689112608710" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1689112608710"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Nike is well-known as a brand for its commitment to product innovation. Performance is at the forefront of their shoe design procedure. Nike rigorously tests their shoes through a wide range of training movements before releasing them to the public. Examples of performance-enhancing design features include their reactive foam for added cushioning and flywire for lightweight support.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1689112621257" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1689112621257" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">✅ Versatile Uses</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1689112630658" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-